4:
Can you hear it? This song means a
lot to you, doesn't it?
6: Wake up, or you'll miss the concert!
11:
...Right, I was... hanging out with the
people here...
13:
Th-thank goodness you're back to
normal!
21:
Oh, come on! You're not getting
away that easy!
35: We have to... protect our song!
50: The rest is up to you.
59:
I can sense... everyone's voices in
them...
77:
Am I... dreaming? Isn't that thing
from Odaiba?
79: Haha, no way... It's the real deal!
81:
Get that ugly thing! Show it who's
boss!
85:
Hehehe... Hahahaha! This is simply
mind-blowing!
88:
You Shibuyans really know how to
do it in style!
91:
It's time to show the world what
you're made of, Amicitia!
96:
H-huh? How did... Are we inside the
robot?!
101: I'm not sure? I think so!
105:
Everyone's fervent desire to protect
your song gave life to this creation!
112: There's still a part of me that's afraid.
121:
As long as we work together, there's
nothing we can't overcome!
132: And blast all our worries away!
144:
Thanks, everyone! We couldn't have
done it without you!
149:
We did it, Hibiki. What'd you think?
Wasn't it a thrill to perform?
157:
Mission accomplished, too! Your
song touched everyone here!
163: Everyone came out safe and sound.
176:
Same. But hey, everything worked
out in the end, right?
181:
I wish that were the case. Despite
avoiding the worst case scenario,
this was a disaster.
194:
We brought our peoples together. In
that regard, I think we can call this
festival a success.
202:
Hibiki, what are your plans going
forward?
206:
I'm not entirely sure yet, but there is
one thing I'd like to do over—
211:
The Kingdom of Mirea is currently
looking to hire an imperial court
musician!
219:
You'll get a guaranteed two days off
a week! Plus the work environment is
relaxed and friendly! We even have
barbecues every weekend—
227:
Could you please refrain from
bothering my favorite musician?
She has her own music to make.
230:
Hibiki, if you ever find yourself having
a hard time in Shibuya, you are
always welcome to come to me.
234:
I'll furnish you with everything you
could possibly need.
239:
I think I'll pass on both options,
thanks.
242:
Luciada! Sorry, do you have a
moment?
244:
We've, uh, got a lot of people
requesting for a redo of the concert.
247:
Ah... That's understandable, given
the chaos of the original
performance.
250: Unfortunately, the stage is in ruins...
255: We can still make it work!
263: I'm in. I... want to do it.
271:
Our first step toward a wonderful
future together!
